Thanks for this one -- it's bad cinema at its best! Like some of the others here I had no luck getting this file to play on some players. I dropped the file into an AVI repair utility and it couldn't repair it, but it reported that it was an MKV file! So I simply changed the "avi" in the file name to "mkv" and now it plays fine in all my players.
